Key Match Events: Edward Cabrera pitched seven scoreless innings
Nick Fortes chased Johnson with a run-scoring double
Norby capped the outburst with his second two-run homer
Seth Johnson allowed nine runs and eight hits in 2 1/3 innings
Post-Match Reflections: Cabrera stated he was aware of the no-hit attempt but focused on performing inning by inning
Cabrera mentioned not wanting to miss more time due to migraines
Manager Skip Schumaker emphasized taking the split series against a contender
Bryce Harper had two hits, including an RBI single in the ninth
Miscellaneous Highlights: Miami ended the major league debut of Philadelphia starter Seth Johnson with a seven-run third inning
Norby homered for the second consecutive day in the first inning
Miami had their 69th player appear in a game this season, tying a major league record
Phillies placed INF Edmundo Sosa (back spasms) on the 10-day injured list
Marlins LHP Ryan Weathers gave up four runs and six hits over 2 2/3 innings in a rehab outing
